meaning: the ability to guide and inspire others toward a common goal
the guidance provided by a mentor, especially an experienced person in a company or educational institution
the assignment of responsibility and authority to another person
the reason or reasons one has for acting or behaving in a particular way
the process of being mentally stimulated to do or feel something
the process of giving someone the authority or power to do something
the fact or condition of being accountable; responsibility
the quality of being open and honest; easy to perceive or detect
the quality of being honest and having strong moral principles
the quality of being trusted and believed in
